node.statement: PART (b) â€” RESIDUE MATCHING. Continuing from node 1.6.4, expand 1/(omega_1_prime * t * (1 + (omega_1_double_prime/(2*omega_1_prime))*t + ...)) = (1/(omega_1_prime * t)) * (1 - (omega_1_double_prime/(2*omega_1_prime))*t + O(t^2)). Therefore nG_p(omega_1(z)) = 1/(omega_1_prime(nu_k) * (z - nu_k)) + [H_p(lambda_{sigma(k)}) - omega_1_double_prime(nu_k)/(2*omega_1_prime(nu_k)^2)] + O(z - nu_k). Meanwhile, nG_r(z) = 1/(z - nu_k) + H_r(nu_k) + O(z - nu_k). Since G_r(z) = G_p(omega_1(z)) (subordination identity, node 1.5(a)), we match the Laurent series at z = nu_k. Matching the coefficient of (z - nu_k)^{-1}: 1/omega_1_prime(nu_k) = 1, hence omega_1_prime(nu_k) = 1. By identical argument with omega_2 and G_q: omega_2_prime(nu_k) = 1. This holds for all k = 1,...,n, completing part (b).
